==English==

===Noun===
'''enneagon'''

#a [[polygon]] with nine sides; a [[nonagon]].

====Synonym====
*[[nonagon]]

====Usage note====
While '''enneagon''' is etymologically consistent with [[pentagon]], [[hexagon]], etc, it is rarely used; '''nonagon''' is the preferred term.

====Translations====
*French: [[ennéagone]] ''m''

